Abuja Nigeria's army has captured a key Boko Haram camp that was the Islamist militant group's last enclave in its northeastern Sambisa forest stronghold, President Muhammadu Buhari said on Saturday.&quot;I was told by the Chief of Army Staff that the camp fell at on Friday and that the terrorists are on the run and no longer have a place to hide,&quot; said Buhari.The Nigerian military has in recent weeks been carrying out a large-scale offensive in the Sambisa forest, a vast former colonial game reserve that has been the group's base. Reuters